Okay, here's a tip from an ex internet narc: Make sure that you set your uploads to '0'.  Basically, it is not illegal to take something that someone wants to give you for free, just don't get caught giving away something that you don't have the rights to. Limewire should work for ya.  See if you can get an older version.  Quite often they work better.
FTR - Private messages are better for this type of discussion.
AVG is a good & free anti-virus too.

The real answer is... forget about McAfee, forget about Norton and forget about Limewire. For virus protection, use AVG free. For any type of download that you heart desires, discover what torrents are and how to use them. Mind you I don't do any of this. It's just what I've heard.

It never hurts to remove spyware, tracking software (cookies), etc...  a good program for cleaning that stuff up is Ad-Aware SE.  You can download it for free from:  http://www.download.com/Ad-Aware-2007-Free...dl&tag=top5  Install, and then do a full system scan.  When it completes select all entries and remove them, and it will probably ask you to reboot.  Sometimes it can take 2 scans to clean up everything but your PC performance will likely improve after running the scan.  Tony
